\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{1}

\part Find the value of

\begin{subparts}
\subpart $\sqrt[3]{3375}$,

\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{1}

\subpart $12^0$.

\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{1}

\end{subparts}

\part Rana hires a car.

The cost is \$74 per day plus a delivery cost of \$17.50\,.

Rana pays a total of \$461.50\,.

Calculate the number of days that Rana hires the car.

\AnswerLine[][days]
\Marks{2}

\part A train to town $A$ leaves a station every 25 minutes.

A train to town $B$ leaves the same station every 45 minutes.

Both trains leave at 08\,00.

Find the next time both trains leave together.

\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{3}

\end{parts}

\begin{parts}
\part The table shows the number of items sold to each of 60 customers in a shop.

\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{|c|c|}
\hline
Number of items sold & Frequency \\
\hline
0 & 3 \\
\hline
1 & 6 \\
\hline
2 & 12 \\
\hline
3 & 8 \\
\hline
4 & 14 \\
\hline
5 & 10 \\
\hline
6 & 3 \\
